ward the history of sexuality in the Middle East, Producing Desire sheds new light on the history of the Ottoman Empire, on the history of sexuality and gender, and on the Islamic Middle East today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aDesire. 0aSex customsxMiddle East. 0aSex customszMiddle East. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh  aanthropologists.  acultural history.  aeastern societies.  afoucault.  agagnon.  agender studies.  ahistorians.  ahuman nature.  aislamic influence.  alaqueur.  alegal documents.  alust.  amedical texts.  amen and women.  amiddle east history.  amiddle east.  amiddle eastern societies.  amorality.  anonfiction.  aottoman culture.  aottoman empire.  areligious literature.  asex.  asexual desire.  asexual discourse.  asexual history.  asexual thought.  asexuality.  ashadow theater.  atravelogues.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093898440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938984423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938984/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles